  "text": "Quantification of endocytosis was performed as previously described [CITATION_1] . Confluent mPTC were incubated with Alexa488-conjugated gentamicin or Alexa488-conjugated BSA (both at 0.5 mg/mL) for 15 min at 37°C. After incubation, mPTC were washed five times with cold HBSS (4°C) and lysed. The fluorescence in the lysate was measured in a fluorimeter (Perkin Elmer) with excitation at 490±10 nm and emission at 525±10 nm. For metabolic inhibition experiments, mPTC were incubated with 10 mM sodium azide or 50 mM 2-deoxyglucose (DOG) for 30 min at 37°C before the endocytic assay. For competition experiments, mPTC were simultaneously incubated with 50 mM unlabelled albumin or transferrin. Fluorescence was normalized for the amount of protein in the cells, measured using the BCA kit (Pierce, Belgium).",
